"Lempert R.J.","A new decision sciences for complex systems",2002,"Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America","99","SUPPL. 3",,"7309","7313",,,10.1073/pnas.082081699,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037076360&partnerID=40&md5=01f2ee4e1700293f9d41769165eba8ee","RAND, 1700 Main Street, Santa Monica, CA 90407, United States","Lempert, R.J., RAND, 1700 Main Street, Santa Monica, CA 90407, United States","Models of complex systems can capture much useful information but can be difficult to apply to real-world decision-making because the type of information they contain is often inconsistent with that required for traditional decision analysis. New approaches, which use inductive reasoning over large ensembles of computational experiments, now make possible systematic comparison of alternative policy options using models of complex systems. This article describes Computer-Assisted Reasoning, an approach to decision-making under conditions of deep uncertainty that is ideally suited to applying complex systems to policy analysis. The article demonstrates the approach on the policy problem of global climate change, with a particular focus on the role of technology policies in a robust, adaptive strategy for greenhouse gas abatement.","Agent-based modeling; Complex adaptive systems; Computer-assisted reasoning; Deep uncertainty; Robust adaptive planning","accuracy; adaptation; article; computer analysis; computer model; decision making; decision theory; environmental protection; global climate; greenhouse gas; information processing; policy; priority journal; technology",,,,,,"Dawes, R., (1988) Rational Choice in an Uncertain World, , Harcourt Brace Jovanovich, San Francisco; Schwartz, P., (1996) The Art of the Long View, , Doubleday, Garden City, NY; Van der Heijden, K., (1996) Scenarios: The Art of Strategic Conversation, , Wiley, New York; Bankes, S.C., Lempert, R.J., Popper, S.W., (2001) Comput. Sci. Ind., 3, pp. 71-77; Bankes, S.C., (1993) Oper. Res., 41, pp. 435-449; Van Asselt, M.B.A., (2000) Perspectives on Uncertainty and Risk, p. 434. , Kluwer, Boston; Lempert, R.J., Schlesinger, M.E., (2000) Clim. Change, 45, pp. 387-401; Caseman, E.A., Morgan, M.G., Dowlatabadi, H., (1999) Risk Anal., 19, pp. 33-42; Rotmans, J., De Vries, H.J.M., (1997) Perspectives on Global Change: The TARGETS Approach, , Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge, U.K; Watson, S.R., Buede, D.M., (1987) Decision Synthesis: The Principles and Practices of Decision Analysis, , Cambridge Univ. Press, New York; Rosenhead, M.J., Elton, M., Gupta, S.K., (1972) Oper. Res. Q., 23, pp. 413-430; Brooks, A., Bankes, S.C., Bennett, B., (1999) Mil. Oper. Res., 4, pp. 67-80; Szayna, T.C., Byman, D.L., Bankes, S.C., Eaton, D., Jones, S.G., Mullins, R.E., Lesser, I.O., Rosenau, W., (2001) The Emergence of Peer Competitors: A Framework for Analysis, , (RAND), MR-1346-A; Dewar, J.A., Bankes, S.C., Edwards, S.J.A., Wendt, J.C., (2000) Expandability of the 21st Century Army, , (RAND), MR-1190-A; Davis, P.K., Carrillo, M.J., (1997) Exploratory Analysis of the Halt Problem: A Briefing on Methods and Initial Insights, , (RAND), DB-232; Lempert, R.J., Bonomo, J., (1998) New Methods for Robust Science and Technology Planning, , (RAND), DB-238-DARPA; Lempert, R.J., Schlesinger, M.E., Bankes, S.C., (1996) Clim. Change, 33, pp. 235-274; Robalino, D.A., Lempert, R.J., (2000) Integr. Assess., 1, pp. 1-19; Lempert, R.J., Schlesinger, M.E., Bankes, S.C., Andronova, N.G., (2000) Clim. Change, 45, pp. 129-161; Park, G., Lempert, R.J., (1998) The Class of 2014, Preserving Access to California Higher Education, , (RAND), MR-971","Lempert, R.J.; RAND, 1700 Main Street, Santa Monica, CA 90407, United States; email: lempert@rand.org",,,,,,,,00278424,,PNASA,12011411,"English","Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0037076360
